AUM-Ø Metal kernels — attribution
==================================

This directory builds the AUM-Ø Apple-Silicon (Metal/MPS) kernels standalone, with no dependency
on the ThunderMittens repository at build or runtime.

Vendored substrate (header-only MSL, in ./include/):
  Derived from ThunderMittens (an Apple Metal Shading Language port of ThunderKittens,
  HazyResearch, https://github.com/HazyResearch/ThunderKittens). These are the reusable
  tile/type/op primitives (`tk.metal` and the common/, ops/, types/ trees). Periodically synced
  from the ThunderMittens working tree; unmodified here.

Kernel sources (in ./src/):
  - mamba2.metal      : SSD forward (quadratic materialized), the chunked LINEAR-TIME pipeline
                        (ssd_chunk_kv/scan/out + the gstate/rscan/bwd_row/bwd_col backward),
                        64x64 quadrant-tiled and COOPERATIVE (threadgroup-per-chunk state
                        staging), D in {64,128}; plus the quadratic backward
                        (mamba2_bwd_row/col). Derived from ThunderMittens' mamba2 kernel; the
                        chunked-pipeline extensions were built here and port back (see the
                        session port-back notes).
  - aum_unfold.metal  : the AUM-only fused U-phase operand pipeline (aum_operands: rotation
                        ladder + k/v L2-norms + rho*tau + layout transpose; aum_epilogue:
                        D-skip + gated RMSNorm + transpose back). Written for AUM-Ø.
  - cross_entropy.metal : fused CE fwd/bwd over the vocab axis (loss+lse; never materializes
                        probabilities; ignore_index / label smoothing / z-loss / softcap; 1- and
                        4-simdgroup-per-row variants). Vendored verbatim from ThunderMittens.

Host dispatch (./aum_metal.mm) and build (./__init__.py):
  Written for AUM-Ø; the generic torch-MPS encoder/plumbing follows ThunderMittens' tk_torch
  pattern (torch::mps command-stream dispatch), inlined here so the build is self-contained.

